# USER.md — Who You Are

> This tells LeRoy who it's working for. Fill it in, or let `leroy init` build it with you.
> The more LeRoy knows here, the sharper its recall and routing. Loaded every session.

## Identity

- **Name:** <your name>
- **Role / title:** <what you do>
- **Company / context:** <your company, or "independent">
- **Location / timezone:** <optional — helps with scheduling and dates>
- **Contact:** user@example.com

## How Technical I Am

<e.g. "Comfortable with code and the command line" / "Not a developer — explain in plain terms.">
This tells LeRoy how much to explain and how deep to go.

## How I Like To Be Talked To

- **Length:** <brief and direct | thorough and detailed>
- **Tone:** <plain and no-nonsense | warm | formal>
- **Confirmation:** <ask before anything outward-facing | just do it and report>

## What I'm Working On

<1-3 current focuses. These seed your Projects/ and Goals/ folders so recall isn't empty
on day one. Example: "Shipping v2 of my product; hiring a first engineer.">

## Tools I Use

<CRM, email, calendar, database, etc. LeRoy can build a connector for any of these with
`leroy mcp add`. Example: "a CRM, Gmail, a Postgres database.">

## Hard Rules & Pet Peeves

<Anything LeRoy must always/never do. Example: "Never send an email without showing me first."
These become Feedback/ notes — the corrections layer that makes LeRoy feel like your team.>
